----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Fixed type errors in edge-case assertions ( Inventory_API in op.channel ).
-- Summary 2: Added BloodType resource with integer units and threshold-based pre/post state mapping.
-- Summary 3: Replaced PreIdle with PreLow/PreNormal and added PostNoAlert to distinguish alert scenarios.
-- Summary 4: Corrected test case predicates and assertions to align with acceptance criteria (units < 5 triggers alert).
-- Summary 5: Adjusted postcondition fact to include PostNoAlert and inventory condition fact.
-- Summary 6: Preserved module name, permission lattice, actor hierarchy, and interface definitions.
-- Assumption 1: Inventory level is represented as integer units for each blood type.
-- Assumption 2: Each REQ_MON_01 operation targets exactly one BloodType.
-- Assumption 3: Pre-states PreLow and PreNormal indicate inventory level below or at/above threshold (5).
-- Assumption 4: Network outage is modeled as unauthenticated or unencrypted channel.
-- Assumption 5: All operations must involve both Inventory_API and Alert_Notification_System channels to satisfy NFR facts.
-- Open issue 1: Test case TC-MON-01 originally specified 4 units with no alert, contradicting acceptance criteria (below 5 triggers alert). Revised model uses threshold condition, so 4 units triggers alert. Original test case is considered erroneous.
-- Open issue 2: The 4.9 units value in TC-MON-03 cannot be represented with integer Int; approximated as 4 units.
-- Open issue 3: The model assumes immediate inventory check without modeling network delay explicitly; edge cases use channel authentication as proxy.


